						               													<description>Ikra has been designed to be a fun way of introducing or reinforcing Islam in any group of any size. The primary objective in introducing this product is that it should be both entertaining and educational - for every kind of Muslim.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As Muslims come from every geographical area, and from every different culture, we hope that Ikra gives all Muslims an appreciation for their different brothers and sisters, and helps each type address some of the problems specific to themselves as individuals. A few questions have been included in Ikra to show a contrast with Islam. This can initiate interesting discussion and can help us understand the place of Muslims in the world view at least a little more, insha-Allah. As such, there is something in Ikra for everybody!&amp;#10;-In game summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ikra is a game where the goal is the reach the center of the board by answering 1 of 3 questions on a given card and moving a player token counter-clockwise. Questions are largely focused on Islamic teachings, culture, and history, with the addition of general science and geography questions included. once the player does a full lap and ends on their &amp;quot;ladder,&amp;quot; they can answer a corresponding question to achieve hat pillar of Islam and go up one rung. Game ends when a player is able to reach the Ka'aba in the center.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
